<TITLE> Two more BNP leaders get bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 3 (bdnews24.com)--The High Court on Sunday granted bail to former BNP lawmakers Abul Khair Bhuiyan and Shahidul Islam Master in separate cases. A High Court bench of Justice Sharif Uddin Chaklader and Justice Md Imdadul Haque Azad granted them ad interim bail. The bench granted bail to Bhuiyan, former MP from Laxmipur, until charge framing in two extortion cases. Former MP from Jhenidah, Shahidul Islam was granted bail until charge framing in a case involving embezzlement of relief CI sheets. The High Court also issued show cause notices on the government and the Anticorruption Commission asking them to explain why the two former lawmakers should not be awarded permanent bail. The High Court same bench had earlier in the day granted bail to ailing former finance minister M Saifur Rahman. It also awarded bail on the same day to Chhatra Dal president Azizul Bari Helal in case filed under Emergency Powers Rules, and to Laila Arjumand Banu, wife of former Khulna mayor Sheikh Tayebur Rahman, until charge framing in a Tk 15 lakh embezzlement case. bdnew
